<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 Wood Pulp/20:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-03T23:00:00+01:00">June
                                        3, 1940—11 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 3—6:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1494. I have seen Halifax<note n="67" xml:id="d51fn67">British
                                    Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs.</note> regarding your
                                1042, May 31, 4 p.m., and he feels of course there will be no
                                difficulty from the British point of view, but we are following it
                                up. Appropriate Foreign Office officials stated later that it would
                                be very helpful to them to know from what ports in Sweden the ships
                                carrying Swedish cargoes to the United States will sail.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>